d32d40ac-0cd8-4009-b108-0bf2f48b9894.title: HEAD
d32d40ac-0cd8-4009-b108-0bf2f48b9894.definition: Part Division 1 classifies the uppermost parts of the body. This region consists of the skull, its contents, and related external structures.

ec027834-2707-4389-9184-ef038414cc23.title: Head— unspecified
ec027834-2707-4389-9184-ef038414cc23.definition: Injuries to the head where the specific region is unspecified.
ec027834-2707-4389-9184-ef038414cc23.includes: Nonfatal gunshot wounds when a specific head location or brain injury is unspecified
ec027834-2707-4389-9184-ef038414cc23.excludes: Gunshot involving a brain injury regardless of entry point on head (111); Head amputation or decapitation (19)

f4a2ef70-b910-47fe-aca4-4294918c64fd.title: Cranial region
f4a2ef70-b910-47fe-aca4-4294918c64fd.definition: This major group classifies the region that is bordered by the face in front and the neck below and includes the back and top of the head.
f4a2ef70-b910-47fe-aca4-4294918c64fd.includes: Brain and brain stem; hair and scalp, skin of the head; occipital, parietal, and temporal bones

e209fd46-de95-4b39-9b93-10bbde9d03f7.title: Scalp
e209fd46-de95-4b39-9b93-10bbde9d03f7.definition: This code describes the external covering of skull from forehead to neck and from ear to ear.
e209fd46-de95-4b39-9b93-10bbde9d03f7.includes: Scalp; hair; skin of the head

3a7d0818-bb12-4287-b5a3-d28909053e8b.title: Skull
3a7d0818-bb12-4287-b5a3-d28909053e8b.definition: This code describes the bone structure of head from forehead to neck and from ear to ear.
3a7d0818-bb12-4287-b5a3-d28909053e8b.includes: Occipital, parietal, and temporal bones; fatal gunshot wounds

8d216e9e-470c-4561-a73e-7af8e3598561.title: Multiple cranial structures
8d216e9e-470c-4561-a73e-7af8e3598561.definition: Use this code when more than one part in 11 is affected.

e2d78162-a81e-4083-942f-7e635f006e83.title: Ear(s), facial region
e2d78162-a81e-4083-942f-7e635f006e83.definition: Part Group 12 classifies the sensing organs of the head, including eyes, ears, nose and mouth.

3899925d-8bb4-4dd5-a1b6-d02b06fd6010.title: Ear(s)
3899925d-8bb4-4dd5-a1b6-d02b06fd6010.definition: This major group classifies the sense or receptor organs located on either side of the head. The code can be used when either one or both ears are affected. This code applies to traumatic injuries and diseases and disorders.
3899925d-8bb4-4dd5-a1b6-d02b06fd6010.includes: Anvil; auditory nerve; auricle or pinna (or outer ear); cochlea; concha; eardrum; earlobe; eustachian tube; hammer; helix; lobule; middle ear or tympanic cavity; outer ear canal; scapha; semicircular canals; stirrup (stapes); tragus

77cf6177-ea30-445a-8cc7-3978c05feb87.title: Eye(s)
77cf6177-ea30-445a-8cc7-3978c05feb87.definition: This code classifies the sense organs of sight located in the frontal portion of the head. The code can be used for either one or both eyes and when loss or impairment of sight is involved and no specific body part is named. This code applies to traumatic injuries and diseases and disorders.
77cf6177-ea30-445a-8cc7-3978c05feb87.includes: Conjunctiva; cornea; eyeball; inside and outside of the eyelids; iris; lacrimal glands; lens; optic nerve; orbital muscles and bones; retina; upper and lower eyelashes

1a4e2f08-bea0-451b-a2e2-8ec95560b0e0.title: Nose, nasal cavity
1a4e2f08-bea0-451b-a2e2-8ec95560b0e0.definition: This code classifies the internal and external nose as the organ of smell and as a part of the respiratory system. This code applies to traumatic injuries and diseases and disorders.
1a4e2f08-bea0-451b-a2e2-8ec95560b0e0.includes: Nasal bone and cartilage; nasal cavity; Nasopharynx; nasal passage(s); sinus(es); septum; multiple internal locations

530eca4d-e8a4-4b49-901b-560bb3f670a5.title: Mouth
530eca4d-e8a4-4b49-901b-560bb3f670a5.definition: This part of body group classifies the opening of the alimentary canal which houses the tongue and teeth. It is bounded by the lips.
530eca4d-e8a4-4b49-901b-560bb3f670a5.includes: "Inside of mouth" or  "left/right side of mouth" with no further information

62cf7cab-13af-44b8-a379-979624248581.title: Tooth (teeth)
62cf7cab-13af-44b8-a379-979624248581.includes: Molar(s); root of tooth; tooth enamel

27245aa4-5a94-4a8c-8212-4dcf25c069a9.title: Multiple mouth locations
27245aa4-5a94-4a8c-8212-4dcf25c069a9.definition: Select this code if more than one part in 124 is affected.

4e454437-b442-43c3-8ce6-e5f940e78e84.title: Forehead, temple(s)
4e454437-b442-43c3-8ce6-e5f940e78e84.definition: This code classifies the exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the forehead. This is the region extending from the eyebrows to the typical hairline area.

e4f2ced8-4270-48a3-b03a-0c41b4ba1be6.title: Cheek(s)
e4f2ced8-4270-48a3-b03a-0c41b4ba1be6.definition: This code classifies the exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the cheeks
e4f2ced8-4270-48a3-b03a-0c41b4ba1be6.includes: Side of face; zygomatic arch, cheekbones

a30fd515-9b5d-44ed-b070-8c6cf3893f0f.title: Jaw, chin
a30fd515-9b5d-44ed-b070-8c6cf3893f0f.definition: This code classifies the exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the jaw and chin

2da0d18a-313e-4506-918c-1789af21a8e3.title: Multiple ear(s), facial regions
2da0d18a-313e-4506-918c-1789af21a8e3.definition: Select this code if more than one part in 12 is affected.

c82a763b-22e0-4f01-ab95-5f7fb5f8e026.title: Multiple regions of the head
c82a763b-22e0-4f01-ab95-5f7fb5f8e026.definition: This code should be used when a combination of more than one part in Division 1 is affected and not covered by a more specific multiple code.

34706be0-1b4e-46af-94a2-1c62210848e6.title: Other part of head— n.e.c.
34706be0-1b4e-46af-94a2-1c62210848e6.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in Division 1.
34706be0-1b4e-46af-94a2-1c62210848e6.includes: Amputation at the head or decapitation

317fa51a-1b43-4f44-837d-fe787b7f1664.title: NECK
317fa51a-1b43-4f44-837d-fe787b7f1664.definition: Part Division 2 classifies the portion of the body that connects the head to the torso or trunk. This region is bounded by the jaw, chin and cranial region to the top and the shoulder below.

b26a1d72-5f22-434a-960d-de27a2ac5fd2.title: Exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the neck
b26a1d72-5f22-434a-960d-de27a2ac5fd2.definition: The external and musculoskeletal portions of the neck including the uppermost portion of the vertebra. If internal versus external and musculoskeletal structures of the neck is unknown, select this code.
b26a1d72-5f22-434a-960d-de27a2ac5fd2.includes: Cervical vertebrae C1 – C7; cartilage; muscle; skin; subcutaneous tissue;  cervical spine; cervical discs; atlanto-occipital joint; atlanto-axial joint; spinal cord

6265e3f1-7297-4599-911f-f745b29a6355.title: Internal neck structures
6265e3f1-7297-4599-911f-f745b29a6355.definition: The underlying visceral structures of the neck. This includes the musculomembranous tube in the back of the nose, mouth, and larynx.  It extends from the skull to the esophagus.
6265e3f1-7297-4599-911f-f745b29a6355.includes: Larynx; pharynx; laryngopharynx; vocal cords; oropharynx; thyroid; parathyroid; and veins and arteries of the neck;

77b7a1b3-10b5-464e-bec2-2cc69e63724a.title: External and internal neck locations
77b7a1b3-10b5-464e-bec2-2cc69e63724a.definition: Use this code when both internal and external neck locations are affected.

615ec962-48d3-44e5-9c5b-75828677b42b.title: TRUNK
615ec962-48d3-44e5-9c5b-75828677b42b.definition: Part Division 3 classifies the main part of the body, where the head and limbs are attached. It includes the external and internal structures and organs. The area is bounded by the neck, shoulders, and legs. The selection of Part is not affected by whether the injury or illness occurred on the right or left side of the body. For example, for “injured rib on right side,” code Chest, except internal location of diseases or disorders (310).

f8a12bf6-80b2-487d-9c4a-cef2ef3ad463.title: Trunk— unspecified
f8a12bf6-80b2-487d-9c4a-cef2ef3ad463.definition: This code classifies instances where it cannot be determined what region of the trunk was affected or whether injuries affected internal organs and structures.
f8a12bf6-80b2-487d-9c4a-cef2ef3ad463.includes: Injury to "side", "torso", or "body" with no other part information;

4fc6a71b-9278-4492-a8db-3c7998a79458.title: Chest— including ribs, internal organs
4fc6a71b-9278-4492-a8db-3c7998a79458.definition: Part group 31 includes the frontal region of the body or thorax. It is bounded by the respiratory diaphragm or abdomen below, the shoulder above, and the back in the rear.

f58f5c7a-76a1-4b68-b6df-9ecbc6000661.title: Chest— unspecified
f58f5c7a-76a1-4b68-b6df-9ecbc6000661.definition: This code classifies instances where it cannot be determined whether injuries affected internal organs and structures.
f58f5c7a-76a1-4b68-b6df-9ecbc6000661.includes: Unspecified internal organs and structures of the chest

2cd7f63b-2fa0-422b-a302-973b462ba109.title: Exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the chest
2cd7f63b-2fa0-422b-a302-973b462ba109.definition: This code classifies the musculoskeletal structures of the frontal chest region. This code should be selected when instances where internal organs and structures of the chest were not affected.
2cd7f63b-2fa0-422b-a302-973b462ba109.includes: Ribs; sternum; xiphoid process; muscles of the frontal chest region; pectoralis major
2cd7f63b-2fa0-422b-a302-973b462ba109.excludes: Internal organs and structures of the trunk; spine; vertebrae; muscles of the back - trapezius, etc.; bones and muscles of the shoulder - deltoid, clavicle etc.

000ad45a-ad63-41ba-a359-f51f746e48ec.title: Exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the chest— unspecified
000ad45a-ad63-41ba-a359-f51f746e48ec.definition: This code classifies the external structures of the frontal chest region. This code should be selected when instances where internal organs and structures of the chest were not affected.
000ad45a-ad63-41ba-a359-f51f746e48ec.excludes: Internal organs and structures of the trunk; spine; vertebrae; muscles of the back - trapezius, etc.; muscles of the shoulder - deltoid, etc.

80d43977-2ecd-4557-ae96-6f22cd0e3384.title: Breast(s)
80d43977-2ecd-4557-ae96-6f22cd0e3384.definition: This code classifies the internal and external breast(s).

f39c38ee-7e71-4544-b25b-b84a879ec6c6.title: Rib(s), oblique area
f39c38ee-7e71-4544-b25b-b84a879ec6c6.includes: Rib cartilage, oblique area, side, flank, 'side of chest'

af5e762d-36bf-49a0-9dee-22a0ad1581c2.title: Multiple exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the chest
af5e762d-36bf-49a0-9dee-22a0ad1581c2.definition: This code should be selected if more than 1 part from 311 is affected.

4b02c3f9-b1c7-4148-b756-b324daab86eb.title: Other exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the chest— n.e.c.
4b02c3f9-b1c7-4148-b756-b324daab86eb.includes: Sternum; xiphoid process; muscles of the frontal chest region; pectoralis major

382c8677-de6f-401b-95ca-6a6f6ddde762.title: Internal respiratory organs
382c8677-de6f-401b-95ca-6a6f6ddde762.definition: Part subgroup 312 refers to the respiratory structures and organs of the chest or thoracic cavity. These codes may be used for traumatic internal injuries where the specific internal structure is named, for example, burns to lungs. If the specific injured organ is unknown, code Part 3120.  Use when the nature of injury or illness named is a member of Division 2 through 6.

825ff8ee-b2ef-42a0-b49e-03ad1358d8ab.title: Internal respiratory organs— unspecified
825ff8ee-b2ef-42a0-b49e-03ad1358d8ab.definition: This code classifies injuries and illnesses limited to the respiratory system where no further information is known.

cfc3e06f-8102-41dc-86af-b9ca99d8482c.title: Trachea
cfc3e06f-8102-41dc-86af-b9ca99d8482c.definition: This code classifies the entire trachea, including portion extending into the neck.

75940d5f-e2c4-4c5c-99fd-dcc01071a794.title: Bronchus
75940d5f-e2c4-4c5c-99fd-dcc01071a794.definition: This code classifies the two large air tubes (left and right sides) that begins at the end of the trachea and branches into the left and right lungs, respectively.

86faa611-d4f0-473d-978d-8a7cec64fc73.title: Multiple respiratory organs
86faa611-d4f0-473d-978d-8a7cec64fc73.definition: This code should be selected if more than 1 part from 312 is affected.

e34785f0-6a97-4e73-9628-431844e53e4b.title: Other internal respiratory organs— n.e.c.
e34785f0-6a97-4e73-9628-431844e53e4b.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in subgroup 312.

a8427f7f-a399-407e-acdf-98b4d902ab47.title: Internal cardiovascular structures of the chest
a8427f7f-a399-407e-acdf-98b4d902ab47.definition: Part subgroup 313 refers to the heart and vascular structures of the chest or thoracic cavity.

ed273d54-4eac-4fca-a327-001728cca27e.title: Internal cardiovascular structures of the chest— unspecified
ed273d54-4eac-4fca-a327-001728cca27e.definition: This code refers to the heart and vascular structures of the chest or thoracic cavity without further information.

a72bc7ea-3413-44f3-96e7-f8ac25c69662.title: Major blood vessels of the trunk
a72bc7ea-3413-44f3-96e7-f8ac25c69662.includes: Aorta (ascending, descending, thoracic, aortal arch); vena cava (superior and inferior); pulmonary arteries and veins; brachiocephalic and subclavian arteries
a72bc7ea-3413-44f3-96e7-f8ac25c69662.excludes: Carotid artery (22); abdominal aorta (339); minor blood vessels; blood vessels not in trunk should be coded to their respective external region of the body (e.g. femoral artery should be coded as leg)

a3140704-b817-4e79-bd15-763bcee74d71.title: Multiple internal chest locations
a3140704-b817-4e79-bd15-763bcee74d71.definition: This code should be selected if respiratory and circulatory organs/structures were affected.
a3140704-b817-4e79-bd15-763bcee74d71.includes: Injuries and illnesses to respiratory and cardiovascular systems

3c197d7c-09ad-4ef7-aae2-1fe94f4473a7.title: Other internal chest location— n.e.c.
3c197d7c-09ad-4ef7-aae2-1fe94f4473a7.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in group 31.
3c197d7c-09ad-4ef7-aae2-1fe94f4473a7.excludes: Other exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the chest— n.e.c. (3119)

a72bbe64-c632-4b08-93e5-6f53ee1785e1.title: Exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the back
a72bbe64-c632-4b08-93e5-6f53ee1785e1.definition: Part group 32 includes the musculoskeletal structures of the posterior part of the trunk that is bounded by the neck and the pelvis.
a72bbe64-c632-4b08-93e5-6f53ee1785e1.includes: Cartilage, muscles, nerves, and neuroglia of the spine and spinal cord (except cervical); tendons, veins and arteries, of the back; vertebra (backbone) and discs, except cervical
a72bbe64-c632-4b08-93e5-6f53ee1785e1.excludes: Neck or cervical vertebrae – C1 - C7, cervical spine, cervical discs (21); internal organs and structures of the trunk

7c0dacb6-bfab-48dd-905e-6f0c4664cfa5.title: Exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the back— unspecified

9f03bb83-1fab-499f-982d-18d10ff79bce.title: Back— thoracic region
9f03bb83-1fab-499f-982d-18d10ff79bce.definition: This code classifies the region of the back that includes the 12 vertebrae (T1 – T12) on the spinal column located just below the cervical vertebrae of the neck.

2a2ca34f-9a98-43b8-84c0-dec13c6a8ef7.title: Back— lumbar region
2a2ca34f-9a98-43b8-84c0-dec13c6a8ef7.definition: This code classifies the region of the back that includes the five vertebrae (L1 – L5) on the spinal column located in the lower portion of the back.

37bfc5cb-2925-48dc-8a08-e8894ebbab0b.title: Back— sacral region
37bfc5cb-2925-48dc-8a08-e8894ebbab0b.definition: This code classifies the region of the back that includes the five fused bones (S1 – S5) located just below the lumbar region.

73d13b46-0701-44fc-9c92-83759e0e4d5f.title: Back— coccygeal region
73d13b46-0701-44fc-9c92-83759e0e4d5f.definition: This code classifies the region of the back that includes the four fused bones (CO1 – CO4) also known as the tailbone.

cc417237-a5cd-4af2-9ab4-06eedbce3a83.title: Back— multiple regions
cc417237-a5cd-4af2-9ab4-06eedbce3a83.definition: This code should be selected if more than 1 part from 32 is affected.

752fab28-eec5-470a-ac12-047f41f3775e.title: Abdomen
752fab28-eec5-470a-ac12-047f41f3775e.definition: Part group 33 includes that portion of the body which lies between the thorax and the pelvis.

89393e0f-b317-4523-a308-3c2819d86f7b.title: Exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the abdomen
89393e0f-b317-4523-a308-3c2819d86f7b.definition: This code classifies the exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the frontal abdominal region. This code should be selected when instances where internal organs and structures of the abdomen were not affected.
89393e0f-b317-4523-a308-3c2819d86f7b.includes: Rectus abdominus; obliques and other abdominal muscles; soft and connective tissues of the abdominal wall; umbilicus

ce3b395e-dfb9-45c7-bf73-f2ddbedb5cc8.title: Digestive structures (except intestines)
ce3b395e-dfb9-45c7-bf73-f2ddbedb5cc8.definition: Part subgroup 332 includes the underlying visceral structures of the abdomen. These codes may be used for traumatic internal injuries where the specific internal structure is named for example a ruptured spleen.  Use when the nature of injury or illness named is a member of Division 2 through 6 of the Nature of Injury or Illness structure.

65a021b2-50a8-4a73-80cd-0f5523dd9929.title: Multiple digestive structures
65a021b2-50a8-4a73-80cd-0f5523dd9929.definition: This code should be selected if more than 1 part from 331 is affected.

dd4d3efd-d606-4dd7-9289-3e6d5b0319fa.title: Other digestive structures— n.e.c.
dd4d3efd-d606-4dd7-9289-3e6d5b0319fa.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in subgroup 332.

aa917077-2af2-4797-a0ad-da6ab3dad898.title: Intestines, peritoneum
aa917077-2af2-4797-a0ad-da6ab3dad898.definition: Part subgroup 333 includes the underlying visceral structures of the abdomen.

ad590ddc-b56e-4dd2-a426-8b08e0433eb3.title: Large intestine, colon, rectum
ad590ddc-b56e-4dd2-a426-8b08e0433eb3.includes: Ascending, transverse, descending and sigmoid colon; rectum; inner and outer sphincters; diverticula; appendix

2822b40c-7b4a-43b3-a2a5-02d227868b72.title: Multiple intestinal locations
2822b40c-7b4a-43b3-a2a5-02d227868b72.definition: This code should be selected if more than 1 part from 333 is affected.

3f9830d3-6061-47cb-b94d-5241303a4c99.title: Multiple urinary organs
3f9830d3-6061-47cb-b94d-5241303a4c99.definition: This code should be selected if more than 1 part from 334 is affected.

20d17daf-8052-461d-8018-2493bf098f13.title: Other urinary organs— n.e.c.
20d17daf-8052-461d-8018-2493bf098f13.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in subgroup 334.

78576fbf-4a9a-47a1-bbe6-48d2f853fe48.title: Multiple internal abdominal locations
78576fbf-4a9a-47a1-bbe6-48d2f853fe48.definition: This code should be selected if more than 1 part from 33 is affected.

c70f994e-59e0-4cf3-955b-0961c7755b1c.title: Other internal abdominal location— n.e.c.
c70f994e-59e0-4cf3-955b-0961c7755b1c.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in group 33.

4a1e71fa-0d6b-457c-87d2-d2049bcc1cc8.title: Pelvic region
4a1e71fa-0d6b-457c-87d2-d2049bcc1cc8.definition: Part group 34 includes the lower portion of the trunk or torso that supports the lower extremities. This region is bounded by the coccyx of the vertebral column, the abdomen, and the hips/legs.
4a1e71fa-0d6b-457c-87d2-d2049bcc1cc8.excludes: Intestines (333); inguinal region when reported for a hernia (3330)

c21c0491-1f3d-467d-bd55-94ee304cc633.title: Exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the pelvic region
c21c0491-1f3d-467d-bd55-94ee304cc633.definition: Part subgroup 341 classifies the exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the pelvic region. This code should be selected when instances where internal organs and structures of the abdomen were not affected.

d9a1e086-8327-40c1-98f6-740864e97e47.title: Groin
d9a1e086-8327-40c1-98f6-740864e97e47.excludes: Male and female genital regions (342); testes, testicle(s) (3432)

b882c707-2eb8-49c8-a6ad-d9a96bf51f7e.title: Other exterior and musculoskeletal structures of the pelvic region— n.e.c.

954fbe7b-7359-473c-85f5-1bbd190a6816.title: Other external reproductive tract structures— n.e.c.
954fbe7b-7359-473c-85f5-1bbd190a6816.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in subgroup 342.

2b07a59f-813a-472c-8d88-6d985064f4f6.title: Multiple internal reproductive tract structures
2b07a59f-813a-472c-8d88-6d985064f4f6.definition: This code should be selected if more than one part from 343 is affected.

e2dfa82c-bc9a-4db1-8176-62e4c00544f3.title: Other internal reproductive tract structures— n.e.c.
e2dfa82c-bc9a-4db1-8176-62e4c00544f3.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in subgroup 343.

c6630557-7d25-45be-8e1b-59715d5dd588.title: Multiple pelvic region locations
c6630557-7d25-45be-8e1b-59715d5dd588.definition: This code should be selected if more than one part from 34 is affected that isn't covered by a more specific multiple code.
c6630557-7d25-45be-8e1b-59715d5dd588.includes: Internal and external reproductive tract structures

28798786-9ef0-4582-b24e-2ab6c1e31f0b.title: Other part of pelvic region— n.e.c.
28798786-9ef0-4582-b24e-2ab6c1e31f0b.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in group 34.

816d7470-253b-444b-b0c0-9e05a6f00d83.title: Multiple trunk locations
816d7470-253b-444b-b0c0-9e05a6f00d83.definition: This code should be selected if more than one part from 3 is affected that isn't covered by a more specific multiple code.

cccbea95-3ebb-464a-8744-77d3a5ced9ec.title: Other part of trunk— n.e.c.
cccbea95-3ebb-464a-8744-77d3a5ced9ec.definition: This code should be selected if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in division 3.

07304a82-69bc-4392-9142-e7af26cf90cb.title: UPPER EXTREMITIES
07304a82-69bc-4392-9142-e7af26cf90cb.definition: Part Division 4 classifies the extremities that are bounded by the trunk at the top with the fingers as the lowermost part included.
07304a82-69bc-4392-9142-e7af26cf90cb.includes: Bones, cartilage, muscles, skin, subcutaneous tissue, veins and arteries of the upper extremities

4e2b7e0a-9366-4c4d-b963-151af7c5f805.title: Shoulder(s), clavicle(s), scapula(e)
4e2b7e0a-9366-4c4d-b963-151af7c5f805.definition: This code classifies the region where the arm(s) join the trunk and includes the armpit and rotator cuff.
4e2b7e0a-9366-4c4d-b963-151af7c5f805.includes: Clavicle, collar bone, proximal humerus, scapula/shoulder blade, glenoid cavity, shoulder girdle, armpit, underarm, rotator cuff

42024f37-ffab-4c26-806b-891d479bda08.title: Arm(s)
42024f37-ffab-4c26-806b-891d479bda08.definition: Part group 42 includes the upper extremities from the area above the wrist up to the shoulder. Multiple injuries or illnesses to  the same part of body should be coded using the code for that specific part, not a multiple code. Terms like right, left or both are not considered for coding. For example, code several burns that are restricted to the upper part of one or both arms to the Upper arm(s) (421).
42024f37-ffab-4c26-806b-891d479bda08.includes: Mid-shaft and distal parts of the humerus
42024f37-ffab-4c26-806b-891d479bda08.excludes: Hand(s), finger(s) (44); wrist(s) (43); shoulder (41); proximal humerus and armpit (41)

64b32a32-a104-41b7-91dd-1840e7a1078a.title: Wrist(s)
64b32a32-a104-41b7-91dd-1840e7a1078a.definition: This code classifies the region between the forearm and the hand. When the nature of injury or illness named is carpal tunnel syndrome, select this code. If the nature of injury or illness named is amputation, and the point of amputation is the wrist, select Hand(s), except finger(s) (441).
64b32a32-a104-41b7-91dd-1840e7a1078a.excludes: Nature of injury or illness named is amputation, and the point of amputation is the wrist (441)  amputation at wrist (441)

26ace8e2-0e38-40fc-a7b9-06c0f71c19c5.title: Hand(s), finger(s)
26ace8e2-0e38-40fc-a7b9-06c0f71c19c5.definition: Part Group 44 classifies the part of the upper extremity at the end of the wrist.
26ace8e2-0e38-40fc-a7b9-06c0f71c19c5.includes: Hand(s) and finger(s) of the left and right sides

b40b6ed2-ac8c-46a9-a75a-b5fbb3c468e0.title: Hand(s), finger(s)— unspecified
b40b6ed2-ac8c-46a9-a75a-b5fbb3c468e0.includes: “Hand,” with no mention of fingers being included or excluded

fabd3001-d6f8-48de-936c-57626e44b2e6.title: Hand(s), except finger(s)
fabd3001-d6f8-48de-936c-57626e44b2e6.definition: This code classifies the part of the upper extremity at the end of the wrist. Select this code whether the injury or illness involves the left or right hand or both. If the nature of injury or illness named is amputation, and the point of amputation is the wrist or hand, select this code.  Use part code 441 if it is known that only the hand and not the fingers was injured.
fabd3001-d6f8-48de-936c-57626e44b2e6.includes: Knuckles and the areas of the hand between the fingers; palm of hand; tip of hand; back of hand; amputation at wrist

e409355e-c124-4708-a80b-406080b5d579.title: Finger or thumb tip(s), nail(s)
e409355e-c124-4708-a80b-406080b5d579.includes: fingertip(s); nail beds; thumb nail, thumb tip
e409355e-c124-4708-a80b-406080b5d579.excludes: Finger tip and rest of finger(s) or thumb(s)

5a792dde-c0e5-4e19-95cb-25933a767823.title: Thumb(s) and finger(s)
5a792dde-c0e5-4e19-95cb-25933a767823.includes: thumbs and other fingers together, except tips

ef18f5c3-51d6-45c6-9c46-51b0b531029c.title: Other finger(s)— n.e.c.
ef18f5c3-51d6-45c6-9c46-51b0b531029c.definition: Any other part of finger(s), including left and right sides, not classified above in 442.
ef18f5c3-51d6-45c6-9c46-51b0b531029c.includes: Medial phalanx (phalanges);  pointer/index, middle, ring, and/or pinky, except tips; fingers when thumb or fingertip is not specified
ef18f5c3-51d6-45c6-9c46-51b0b531029c.excludes: Thumb(s) (4422); fingernail(s), finger or thumb tip (4421)

c2cf2c34-a6cb-498b-b0ea-0935935291dc.title: Hand(s) and finger(s)
c2cf2c34-a6cb-498b-b0ea-0935935291dc.definition: This code classifies injuries that involve both the hand addition to any section of the thumb(s) and/or finger(s).

6473b158-0328-45a6-a79d-9bce2f0d3e4d.title: Multiple upper extremities locations
6473b158-0328-45a6-a79d-9bce2f0d3e4d.definition: Part group 48 classifies combinations of parts located in two or more subgroups of Division 4.

a5de40f7-3e87-41e2-95df-d0c50742941a.title: Hand(s) and elbow(s)
a5de40f7-3e87-41e2-95df-d0c50742941a.includes: Combination of at least one hand and one elbow

b0d12501-d005-4b69-b45a-9872cd80dce6.title: Hand(s) and arm(s)— n.e.c.
b0d12501-d005-4b69-b45a-9872cd80dce6.includes: Hand and upper and/or lower arm; hand, elbow and arm

faa18c24-6613-4627-a28c-6f21ae4217e7.title: Hand(s) and wrist(s)
faa18c24-6613-4627-a28c-6f21ae4217e7.includes: Combination of at least one hand and one wrist

e839621a-d6a6-4232-8cf8-3addb71b0948.title: Wrist(s) and elbow(s)
e839621a-d6a6-4232-8cf8-3addb71b0948.includes: Combination of at least one wrist and one elbow

d1e333cb-b994-4cae-a9bc-23fee2818794.title: Wrist(s) and arm(s)— n.e.c.
d1e333cb-b994-4cae-a9bc-23fee2818794.includes: Wrist and upper and/or lower arm; wrist, elbow and arm

781884a5-0470-41b6-bde9-1044d5de6265.title: Shoulder(s) and wrist(s)
781884a5-0470-41b6-bde9-1044d5de6265.includes: Combination of at least one shoulder and one wrist

e39eb0ed-c16b-438d-8f62-3bde79ffc3da.title: Multiple upper extremities locations— n.e.c.
e39eb0ed-c16b-438d-8f62-3bde79ffc3da.definition: Select if more than one part from division 4 is affected that is not already classified by a more specific multiple code.

1bd02cf5-45f5-4e2a-9fae-4593d946605e.title: Other upper extremities— n.e.c.
1bd02cf5-45f5-4e2a-9fae-4593d946605e.definition: Select if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in division 4.

9d4df22d-1ae9-4ed6-a2ed-90e9730140a9.title: LOWER EXTREMITIES
9d4df22d-1ae9-4ed6-a2ed-90e9730140a9.definition: Part Division 5 classifies the appendages that includes the hip and extends to the toes as the lowermost part. Codes do not distinguish between the left and the right side of the body.
9d4df22d-1ae9-4ed6-a2ed-90e9730140a9.includes: Bones, cartilage, muscles, skin, subcutaneous tissue, veins and arteries of the lower extremities; amputation at knee

39c4282c-634c-4f9f-8ef0-6d365fe9ce08.title: Hip joint(s)
39c4282c-634c-4f9f-8ef0-6d365fe9ce08.definition: This code describes the hip as the junction point of the trunk and the upper leg that is responsible for upper leg mobility. This code is reserved for injuries that affect the function of the hip joint.
39c4282c-634c-4f9f-8ef0-6d365fe9ce08.includes: Femoral head and neck; hip socket (acetabulum); connective tissues (cartilage, ligaments, tendons) associated with hip function
39c4282c-634c-4f9f-8ef0-6d365fe9ce08.excludes: Pelvic bones (ilium; ischium pubic bones) (341); Pelvic and gluteal muscles (341)

bce0c0d0-21c3-4318-a06b-4b8747139cce.title: Leg(s)
bce0c0d0-21c3-4318-a06b-4b8747139cce.definition: Part group 52 classifies the lower extremities between the hip and the ankle.  Multiple injuries or illnesses to  the same part of body should be coded using the code for that specific part, not a multiple code. Terms like right, left or both are not considered for coding. For example, code several burns that are restricted to the upper part of one or both legs to the thigh(s) (521).

f55feda8-e50f-4858-b098-2efad494705f.title: Thigh(s)
f55feda8-e50f-4858-b098-2efad494705f.includes: Hamstring(s), upper leg(s) If amputated at hip; quadricep(s)  Hamstring(s), upper leg(s); quadricep(s); amputation at hip

4819c943-1122-45a3-bfb3-0228fa825e2e.title: Knee(s)
4819c943-1122-45a3-bfb3-0228fa825e2e.includes: Meniscus, anterior cruciate ligament (ACL), medial collateral ligament (MCL), patella

8fa2207f-febc-418c-8ce2-e5f98252d4b5.title: Knee(s) and leg(s)
8fa2207f-febc-418c-8ce2-e5f98252d4b5.includes: Combination of at least one knee and one leg part

6a230c6e-ea22-4b2e-a94c-5ea183dc1bfd.title: Multiple leg locations— n.e.c.
6a230c6e-ea22-4b2e-a94c-5ea183dc1bfd.definition: Select if more than one part from group 52 is affected that is not already classified by a more specific multiple code.
6a230c6e-ea22-4b2e-a94c-5ea183dc1bfd.includes: Thigh(s) and lower leg(s); whole leg

cfd9ade6-8735-4aae-b5fa-affa07f2f12a.title: Ankle(s)
cfd9ade6-8735-4aae-b5fa-affa07f2f12a.definition: This code classifies the hinge joint area between the foot and the lower leg. If the nature of injury or illness named is amputation, and the point of amputation is ankle, select Foot (feet), n.e.c., (549).

fff08524-f3ba-4e6a-bc25-f983a02cc2f4.title: Foot (feet), toe(s)
fff08524-f3ba-4e6a-bc25-f983a02cc2f4.definition: Part group 54 classifies the lowest extremity of the leg. Select this code if the injury or illness involves the left, right, or both feet.

3cb0ec45-b7d6-416f-b3da-ebb105007ddc.title: Foot (feet), toe(s)— unspecified
3cb0ec45-b7d6-416f-b3da-ebb105007ddc.definition: Select if the source document states foot, with no mention of toes being included or excluded, and the nature is not amputation.

abb34b02-5d75-41dc-8f06-39f6b6c7042f.title: Foot (feet)— excluding toes
abb34b02-5d75-41dc-8f06-39f6b6c7042f.definition: Select if it is known that only the foot and not the toes was injured.
abb34b02-5d75-41dc-8f06-39f6b6c7042f.includes: Sole(s), ball(s) of the foot, arch(es), instep(s), heel(s), multiple sole locations, sole(s), n.e.c.; bottom of foot

a80f7090-8ae8-4daf-ba88-05baeb6cf6c2.title: Toes(s), toenail(s)
a80f7090-8ae8-4daf-ba88-05baeb6cf6c2.definition: This code classifies the digits of the foot.

13552502-6df5-4dc4-a727-b2653626501e.title: Foot (feet) and toe(s)
13552502-6df5-4dc4-a727-b2653626501e.definition: This code classifies instances where the feet and toes are both injured.

0b812f2d-627c-48fe-82de-16a43bd40971.title: Multiple lower extremities locations
0b812f2d-627c-48fe-82de-16a43bd40971.definition: Part group 58 classifies combinations of differing part of the body within the lower extremity division.

2bd93f2c-a76b-4468-9bca-7bbd950c879d.title: Foot (feet) and hip(s)
2bd93f2c-a76b-4468-9bca-7bbd950c879d.definition: Select for injuries that affect the hip and at least one part from group 54.

95e7dbd9-3b77-44d5-8baf-e4ce98b30970.title: Foot(feet) and leg(s)— unspecified
95e7dbd9-3b77-44d5-8baf-e4ce98b30970.definition: Select should be selected for injuries that affect at least one part from group 54 and one from group 52.

4bed850f-7e63-496c-8981-9c31cd8e5772.title: Foot(feet) and knee(s)
4bed850f-7e63-496c-8981-9c31cd8e5772.definition: Select should be selected for injuries that affect at least one part from group 54 and the knee.

fab521b7-666f-423f-929b-3dbe283d2e5d.title: Foot(feet) and leg(s)— n.e.c.
fab521b7-666f-423f-929b-3dbe283d2e5d.definition: Select should be selected if the parts are known, but not covered by a listed code in subgroup 582.
fab521b7-666f-423f-929b-3dbe283d2e5d.includes: Combinations of at least one foot and one leg

61e80d0e-ebdf-4b87-a57e-662a24ba96cc.title: Foot (feet) and ankle(s)
61e80d0e-ebdf-4b87-a57e-662a24ba96cc.definition: Select for injuries that affect at least one part from group 54 and the ankle.
61e80d0e-ebdf-4b87-a57e-662a24ba96cc.includes: Combinations of at least one foot and one ankle

0291e43f-a7d8-4424-bdd3-22803461ca28.title: Ankle(s) and leg(s)— unspecified
0291e43f-a7d8-4424-bdd3-22803461ca28.definition: Select for injuries that affect the ankle and at least one part from group 52.

0fd879b0-b2b2-4c5e-a4b8-56b3c59118df.title: Ankle(s) and leg(s)— n.e.c.
0fd879b0-b2b2-4c5e-a4b8-56b3c59118df.definition: Select if the ankle(s) are affected as well as the upper or lower leg.

073a7ad0-6fb3-415d-a526-15c2f80d8604.title: Hip(s) and leg(s)— unspecified
073a7ad0-6fb3-415d-a526-15c2f80d8604.definition: Select for injuries that affect the hip and at least one part from group 52.

2e579d5c-953b-429f-a521-4b211e1e73d1.title: Hip(s) and leg(s)— n.e.c.
2e579d5c-953b-429f-a521-4b211e1e73d1.definition: Select if the hip(s) are affected as well as the upper or lower leg.

4d656e22-ab79-4e07-a450-045e34427cf6.title: Multiple lower extremities locations— n.e.c.
4d656e22-ab79-4e07-a450-045e34427cf6.definition: Select if more than one part from division 5 is affected that is not already classified by a more specific multiple code.

b582324c-a0aa-45ba-8a8b-579d1294364a.title: Lower extremities— n.e.c.
b582324c-a0aa-45ba-8a8b-579d1294364a.definition: Select if the part is known, but not covered by a listed code in division 5.

d301ac27-b2a2-4196-8909-ef5afdc1a86c.title: BODY SYSTEMS
d301ac27-b2a2-4196-8909-ef5afdc1a86c.definition: Part Division 6 classifies the various systems of the body and applies when the functioning of an entire body system or multiple body systems have been affected without specific injury to any other part of the body. It does not apply when the systemic damage results from an external injury affecting an external part such as a back injury that includes damage to the nerves of the spinal cord. Nor does it apply when the injury or illness is localized and affects a particular internal organ. If the nature of injury or illness selected is a subset of the Division 2, Systemic Diseases and Disorders, the part of body affected is not necessarily body systems. Generally tumors will be coded to the individual body part (or organ) rather than Body systems.
d301ac27-b2a2-4196-8909-ef5afdc1a86c.includes: Psyche; stress responses; "respiratory issues" with no further information.
d301ac27-b2a2-4196-8909-ef5afdc1a86c.excludes: Asphyxiation due to neck (2) or chest (31) compression. Code to external part.

a88ebd3d-cec6-49f5-9852-c0dd95b6ef70.title: MULTIPLE BODY PARTS
a88ebd3d-cec6-49f5-9852-c0dd95b6ef70.definition: Part Division 8 classifies instances where a combination of body parts in more than one division are affected by an injury, disease or disorder. Body part combinations within the same division are classified by multiple codes within that division.

d741fe5d-44d1-4f1b-954c-3dd7fd90d071.title: Multiple body parts— unspecified
d741fe5d-44d1-4f1b-954c-3dd7fd90d071.definition: Select this code when source documents state multiple body parts were affected but do not provide information to select a more detailed code.
d741fe5d-44d1-4f1b-954c-3dd7fd90d071.includes: "left side of body" or "right side of body"

25848c15-6af0-4ca5-9a39-7691299c8290.title: Head and other part(s) of body

709ad042-7f73-40af-87f1-54e38de48074.title: Head and neck
709ad042-7f73-40af-87f1-54e38de48074.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from division 1 and one or more from division 2.

7f86c020-48ce-4654-a7ff-75dced49776d.title: Head and trunk
7f86c020-48ce-4654-a7ff-75dced49776d.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from division 1 and one or more from division 3.

9e763128-9af3-4e37-9676-a9945423d183.title: Head and extremities
9e763128-9af3-4e37-9676-a9945423d183.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from division 1 and parts from divisions 4 and 5.

8a76b43b-6f6d-497a-9d6e-48553253d678.title: Neck and other part(s) of body

e3e2c40b-7822-4e57-941c-3ea428c598c0.title: Neck and back
e3e2c40b-7822-4e57-941c-3ea428c598c0.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from division 2 and one or more parts from group 32.

e89c2abd-f432-40a9-ac18-774b7f037717.title: Neck and shoulder
e89c2abd-f432-40a9-ac18-774b7f037717.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from division 2 and part code 41 - Shoulder

547e6fda-2de5-4e6d-8380-fbb0cc5a4c68.title: Neck and upper extremities
547e6fda-2de5-4e6d-8380-fbb0cc5a4c68.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from division 2 and parts from divisions 4 and 5.

ca5465d0-c3dc-4f56-97e1-2338db11515a.title: Trunk and other part(s) of body

c35e025a-9e6b-4d45-b041-a1ca311a4e04.title: Back and shoulder
c35e025a-9e6b-4d45-b041-a1ca311a4e04.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of part code 41 and one or more from group 32 (back).

6adad0b9-d967-4fec-9a2e-be774aef6dd1.title: Trunk and hip joint(s)
6adad0b9-d967-4fec-9a2e-be774aef6dd1.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from division 3 and part code 51 - Hip joint.

e01e7987-ac74-4d96-99e8-386f54ca9c9c.title: Hands and feet
e01e7987-ac74-4d96-99e8-386f54ca9c9c.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from group 44 - hand(s), finger(s), and one or more parts from group 54 - Foot(feet), toe(s).

5dff8506-63b5-4b44-af0d-1db31b3090e8.title: Upper and lower extremities— n.e.c.
5dff8506-63b5-4b44-af0d-1db31b3090e8.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from division 4, except 44 - hand(s), finger(s), and division 5, except from group 54 - Foot(feet), toe(s).

4550203c-b69c-4de1-a9de-1b3aebb7cfa8.title: Body systems and other part(s) of body
4550203c-b69c-4de1-a9de-1b3aebb7cfa8.definition: Select for injuries that affect a combination of one or more parts from divisions 1-5 and/or 7 and division 6.
4550203c-b69c-4de1-a9de-1b3aebb7cfa8.includes: skin damage and poisoning effects of chemical exposure; burns and smoke inhalation

a013e647-3433-4e01-bd1c-bb56c2c3ee67.title: Whole body
a013e647-3433-4e01-bd1c-bb56c2c3ee67.definition: Select when 80 percent or more of the body is affected.

bd43c46a-1f7f-4545-b5b9-34f900f1286c.title: Part of body— unspecified
bd43c46a-1f7f-4545-b5b9-34f900f1286c.definition: Part code 990 classifies instances when no information about the injured body part is available.
bd43c46a-1f7f-4545-b5b9-34f900f1286c.includes: Skin when no other detail is available
